    {
        "user": "U027JEHGZRA",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1771436893.274109",
        "client_msg_id": "356dbf7a-13ff-4108-a576-3ef7ced2f0ae",
        "text": "Thank you, <@U01JACR6L7L>! I don't think there's any actionable on your end for the time being, but I appreciate the offer and ping :bow:\n\n<@U01DZUA88S1> kindly created a related ticket at <https:\/\/github.com\/r-devel\/rsmf\/issues\/21|https:\/\/github.com\/r-devel\/rsmf\/issues\/21>\n\nI'm sure we will be able to create a test patch no later than early March as a preparation for a final patch before the new R release.\n\nFTR there's no huge tech barrier, as we have helper scripts and the process has been documented, it just needs some polishing and potentially some minor updates -- hopefully can be done in a few hours. We started that at the last R dev day (Durham), but did not manage to finish due to some translations accepted by Weblate, but not passing the R checks -- so we needed to manually track those down and fix. There's still some of that to be done.\n\nAs the team grows, hopefully we can get through it much faster collectively :blush:",
