                                "type": "user",
                                "user_id": "U01DZUA88S1"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " kindly created a related ticket at "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/github.com\/r-devel\/rsmf\/issues\/21",
                                "text": "https:\/\/github.com\/r-devel\/rsmf\/issues\/21"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nI'm sure we will be able to create a test patch no later than early March as a preparation for a final patch before the new R release.\n\nFTR there's no huge tech barrier, as we have helper scripts and the process has been documented, it just needs some polishing and potentially some minor updates -- hopefully can be done in a few hours. We started that at the last R dev day (Durham), but did not manage to finish due to some translations accepted by Weblate, but not passing the R checks -- so we needed to manually track those down and fix. There's still some of that to be done.\n\nAs the team grows, hopefully we can get through it much faster collectively "
